our heart, and the world will tremble."_#',NULL,'Mark Zug','3','4.179','£10/1/2007: Doran’s ability means, for example, that a 2/3 creature will assign 3 damage in combat instead of 2.£10/1/2007: Doran’s ability doesn’t actually change creatures’ power; it changes only the value of the combat damage they assign. All other rules and effects that check power or toughness use the real values.£10/1/2007: This effect is mandatory and affects all creatures.','GWB (O)',NULL,'N/A','9.88','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'WBG',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('244666','Kiki-Jiki, Mirror Breaker','V11','Legendary Creature — Goblin Shaman','M','{2}{R}{R}{R}','5','2','2',NULL,'Haste£{T}: Create a token that''s a copy of target nonlegendary creature you control. That token has haste. Sacrifice it at the beginning of the next end step.',NULL,NULL,'Steven Belledin','4','4.329','£11/17/2017: The token copies exactly what was printed on the creature and nothing else (unless that creature was copying something else or was a token; see below). It doesn’t copy whether that creature was tapped or untapped, whether it had any counters on it or Auras and/or Equipment attached to it, or any non-copy effects that changed its power, toughness, types, color, and so on.£11/17/2017: If the copied creature had {X} in its mana cost, X is 0.£11/17/2017: If the copied creature was copying something else, the tokens enter the battlefield as whatever that creature was copying.£11/17/2017: If the copied creature is a token, the tokens created by Kiki-Jiki’s ability copies the original characteristics of that token as stated by the effect that put it onto the battlefield.£11/17/2017: Any enters-the-battlefield abilities of the copied creature will trigger when the tokens enter the battlefield. Any “As [this creature] enters the battlefield” or “[This creature] enters the battlefield with” abilities of the copied creature will also work.','R',NULL,'N/A','11.19','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'R',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('244672','Kresh the Bloodbraided','V11','Legendary Creature — Human Warrior','M','{2}{B}{R}{G}','5','3','3',NULL,'Whenever another creature dies, you may put X +1/+1 counters on Kresh the Bloodbraided, where X is that creature''s power.','#_Each of his twenty-two braids is bound with bone and leather from a foe._#',NULL,'Steve Argyle','5','3.394','£10/1/2008: X is equal to the power of the creature as it last existed on the battlefield.','GRB (O)',NULL,'N/A','14','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'BGR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('259296','Mikaeus, the Lunarch','V11','Legendary Creature — Human Cleric','M','{X}{W}','1','0','0',NULL,'Mikaeus, the Lunarch enters the battlefield with X +1/+1 counters on it.£{T}: Put a +1/+1 counter on Mikaeus.£{T}, Remove a +1/+1 counter from Mikaeus: Put a +1/+1 counter on each other creature you control.',NULL,NULL,'Steven Belledin','6','3.63',NULL,'W',NULL,'N/A','6.15','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'W',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('259295','Omnath, Locus of Mana','V11','Legendary Creature — Elemental','M','{2}{G}','3','1','1',NULL,'You don''t lose unspent green mana as steps and phases end.£Omnath, Locus of Mana gets +1/+1 for each unspent green mana you have.','#_It gathers against the coming storm._#',NULL,'Mike Bierek','7','3.929','£3/1/2010: You can keep green mana in your mana pool indefinitely while Omnath is on the battlefield. That means if you add a green mana to your mana pool during one step or phase, you can spend it during a later step or phase, or even a later turn. Other types of mana will continue to empty from your mana pool as each step and phase ends.£3/1/2010: If a green mana you add to your mana pool has certain restrictions or riders associated with it (for example, if it was produced by Ancient Ziggurat), they’ll apply to that mana no matter when you spend it.£3/1/2010: Once Omnath leaves the battlefield, you have until the end of the current step or phase to spend whatever green mana is in your mana pool before it too empties as normal. There is no penalty associated with this other than the loss of the mana.','G',NULL,'N/A','17.48','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'G',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('244668','Oona, Queen of the Fae','V11','Legendary Creature — Faerie Wizard','M','{3}{UB}{UB}{UB}','6','5','5',NULL,'Flying£{X}{UB}: Choose a color. Target opponent exiles the top X cards of their library. For each card of the chosen color exiled this way, create a 1/1 blue and black Faerie Rogue creature token with flying.',NULL,NULL,'Adam Rex','8','4.239','£5/1/2008: You target the opponent when you activate Oona’s ability. You don’t choose the color until the ability resolves.£5/1/2008: The tokens enter the battlefield under your control.','UB (H)',NULL,'N/A','6.5','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'UB',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NUL